description: A main category of the subpopulation. A subpopulation can have multiple themes, for health data theme must at least take the value 'Health', which is set as a default

required: if(resource?.hricore === true) 'This field is mandatory for HRICore compatibility'
description: Information that indicates whether the resource is publicly accessible, has access restrictions or is not public. A default is set for non-public access, because most health datasets contain sensitive information and rules and licenses apply to get access

required: if(resource?.hricore === true) 'This field is mandatory for HRICore compatibility'
description: The legislation that mandates the creation or management of the subpopulation. For health datasets, the value must include the data governance act, which is set as a default. URI's to other legislations may be included
A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation
